  • Class Description
    AbstractRuleLoader
    Base class to support loading Rules Related files
    BufferLogger
    An Adaptor that allows us and hold Logs in Memory Useful for Testing
    Cell
    JavaBean equivalent of a cell in an Excel Spreadsheet
    CellConvertor
    Convert from Excel values (as represented by Apache POI) to Javaeans (used by RedPiranha / Rules) and vice versa
    Config
    Set of common functions used by GUI / Command Line / Servlet
    ConsoleLogger
    An Adaptor that allows us to log to the consoles
    ExcelDataExample
    Sample showing how we can read and manipulate data from excel Read Ranges from Excel, Convert to a format that rules can use Based on Sample from Apache POI
    ExcelDataRulesExample
    Sample showing how we can read both data and rules from Excel Read Ranges from Excel, Convert to a format that rules can use Based on Sample from Apache POI
    FileRuleLoader
    Load rules, assume that resources are available on the local file system
    HtmlGenerator
    Utility class for generating HTML used by the GUI
    IGiveFeedbackToUsers
    Marks as class as being able to display a pre and post rules snapshot of Data as feedback to users.
    ILogger
    Marks a class as being one that we can log to.
    IRuleLoader
    Marks a class as being able to load rules on behalf of the system
    PreCompileRuleBuilder
    Pre compile rules, and save them as Drools Knowledge Packages for later (faster) use)
    Range
    A range is just a holder for a group of named cells - maps to a similar Concept in MS Excel We use it as a convenience for loading our values into working memory
    RangeCellTree
    Component we use on our panels to display Ranges and Cells Based on example from @link https://www.codejava.net/java-se/swing/jtree-basic-tutorial-and-examples
    RangeConvertor
    Read Ranges from Excel, Convert to a format (JavaBeans) that rules find easier to use.
    RangeHolder
    Holder of all multiple Named Ranges from a spreadsheet.
    RedCommandLine
    Main Entry Point for Red-Piranha Looks for red-piranha.config to decide what mode it should run in By default, loads data from excel, executes business rules against it, saves into another Excel file.
    RedConstants
    Place holder for System wide Constants
    RedGui
    Desktop GUI for Red Piranha Desktop User interface to ease calling of Rules / running the webserver needed for the office plugin.
    RedSecurityManager
    Simple gatekeeper to ensure we only load resources from known safe locations
    RpLogger
    Extend logging so that we can control logging in an exe environment where we may not have full control of config
    RuleRunner
    Load and Execute business rules
    RuleSource
    Cargo object to hold information about the type of rules that we are working with
    SheetConvertor
    A class that helps up map Excel Worksheets into Javabeans.
    SpreadSheetLogger
    An Adaptor that allows us to log to an Excel File
    SpreadSheetOutputter
    Convenience Class for Output of Spreadhsheets.
    SpreadSheetRuleRunner
    Common Entry point to both Servlet and command line, Call JBoss Drools (Rules Engine) passing in Spreadsheet data as Java Objects This classe specialises in data from excel
    SwingGuiUtils  
    URLRuleLoader
    Load rules from a Web URL
